This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.CL (Computation and Language) as it deals with sequence labeling tasks in a linguistically motivated hierarchy. It also involves the use of neural networks, which is a common technique in the field of natural language processing. 

It could also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it involves the use of a novel neural network algorithm for semi-supervised learning. 

Additionally, it could be categorized under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as it involves the use of machine learning techniques to improve performance on a specific task. 

cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is another possible sub-category as the paper involves the use of neural networks. 

Finally, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is a less likely but still possible sub-category as the paper deals with sequence labeling tasks, which can be applied to tasks such as image segmentation.
